.\" Manpage for lightning(1).
.TH LIGHTNING 1 "May 2026" "scripts" "User Commands"

.SH NAME
lightning \- multi-backend Lightning Network frontend

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lightning
.RI [ options ]
.I command
.RI [ args ...]

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B lightning
is the educational Lightning Network frontend. It
abstracts over multiple lightning daemons so the same
verb surface works across backends:

.TP
.B clightning
The Core Lightning daemon (Blockstream).
.TP
.B lnd
The LND daemon (Lightning Labs).
.TP
.B phoenixd
The lightweight Phoenix daemon (ACINQ).

Each backend plugin lives under
.IR libexec/lightning/<backend>/
and cites the BOLT it implements
(FEAT-178: BOLT 1..11 + LNURL LUDs + Lightning Address
under
.IR share/doc/lightning/standards/ ).

.SH STATUS

The full surface is filed across FEAT-170..182 and
implementation is pending. Today's
.B bin/lightning
is a stub establishing the shape so the artefact set
can land.

.SH SUBCOMMANDS

.TP
.B help / version

.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B SELF_DEBUG
Enable shell tracing.

.SH FILES
.TP
.I libexec/lightning/<backend>/
Per-backend plugin (clightning / lnd / phoenixd).
.TP
.I share/doc/lightning/standards/
Vendored BOLT specs + LNURL LUDs + Lightning Address
spec (FEAT-178, pending).

.SH EXIT STATUS
0 on success; non-zero on failure.

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR account (1),
.BR bitcoin (1),
.BR cluster (1),
.BR secret (1).

.SH STANDARDS
BOLT 1..11 (Lightning Network protocol), LNURL LUDs,
the Lightning Address spec \(em filed for vendoring
under
.IR share/doc/lightning/standards/ .

.SH BUGS
Report at
.UR https://github.com/nostra124/scripts/issues
.UE .
